{"id": "EUVD-2022-55549", "enisaUuid": "51462954-a7f4-34fa-a61d-81d4f7efba18", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\next4: fix potential out of bound read in ext4_fc_replay_scan()\n\nFor scan loop must ensure that at least EXT4_FC_TAG_BASE_LEN space. If remain\nspace less than EXT4_FC_TAG_BASE_LEN which will lead to out of bound read\nwhen mounting corrupt file system image.\nADD_RANGE/HEAD/TAIL is needed to add extra check when do journal scan, as this\nthree tags will read data during scan, tag length couldn't less than data length\nwhich will read.", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T14:46:01", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-23T13:28:07", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6969367c1500c15eddc38fda12f6d15518ad6d03", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f234294812c9b68d603650d28743eafb718e7ad5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1b45cc5c7b920fd8bf72e5a888ec7abeadf41e09", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50306"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50306"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "080f0414-3de8-3b11-905c-9cd5c3c03b24", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "8016e29f4362e285f0f7e38fadc61a5b7bdfdfa2 <1b45cc5c7b920fd8bf72e5a888ec7abeadf41e09"}, {"id": "24978405-3c84-3e90-a8a0-356a0be2eb7e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <f234294812c9b68d603650d28743eafb718e7ad5"}, {"id": "28c9f4c0-6d7c-32d6-b708-11a588c765da", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1"}, {"id": "2d75a0e4-665e-35e1-8898-e743ebbbe7f9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.10"}, {"id": "38c73bf2-8d94-3052-8ef6-e287188c3075", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "3dc65f46-405b-3ca3-8cf0-ce7074de76c7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <6969367c1500c15eddc38fda12f6d15518ad6d03"}, {"id": "42bc9a56-bc8e-3e77-b352-928d49cce